Description:
   Ember Spark is the first practical exercise in the Wizard's Keep curriculum
   — a small, directed burst of Ember Canon fire. Producing it requires
   controlled ignition: proof of will applied to elemental principle. The
   Keep teaches this not as a weapon but as a demonstration of control.

   Damage: 2d4 + level/4, fire elemental. A successful save halves damage.
   Mana cost: 8. Available automatically at level 1.

   As a Magi advances, Ember Spark is superseded by Magic Missile and the
   deeper Ember Canon curriculum (Fireball, Wall of Fire, Lifesteal). It
   remains the first fire the Magi ever commands.
